In order to do this, I first converted my SimpleXML dashboard to the HTML counterpart. Next I was able to modify the JavaScript and added the following requirement and function to make _TableView_ work.

``` javascript
require([
    ...
    "splunkjs/mvc/tableview"
   ...
   ],
   function(
   ...
   TableView
   ...
   )
```

Next I changed the tables on the dashboard from _TableElement_ to _TableView_ in the element specification.

To make the images visible, I made a custom cell renderer that will change the cell content if the corresponding field contains either 'image' or 'picture', assuming that is contains a link to an image, and show the image instead of the link.

``` javascript
var CustomCellRenderer = TableView.BaseCellRenderer.extend({
    canRender: function(cellData) {
        // This method returns "true" for the "image" or "picture" field
        return cellData.field.toLowerCase().includes("image") || cellData.field.toLowerCase().includes("picture");
    },

    // This render function only works when canRender returns "true"
    render: function($td, cellData) {
        console.log("cellData: ", cellData);
        $td.html('<img class="td-image" src="'+cellData.value+'" />');
    }
});
```

Finally, I had to add the _CustomCellRenderer_ to the tables in the dashboard where I want the conversion to be done. In my case I have two tables and had to add the following:
``` javascript
var customCellRenderer = new CustomCellRenderer();

element3.addCellRenderer(customCellRenderer);
element3.render();

element5.addCellRenderer(customCellRenderer);
element5.render();
```

Now when the dashboard is saved and refreshed, the images should be visible.
